    <node id="&quot;TINY TIM&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Timothy Cratchit, Bob Cratchit's youngest son who is crippled and uses crutches to walk."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's disabled son who becomes a symbol of hope and innocence in the story."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob Cratchit's disabled son, known for his cheerful and hopeful demeanor despite his illness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is Bob and Mrs. Cratchit's youngest son who is not concerned about Mr. Scrooge despite being part of the poor family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a child with weak eyes who is loved by his father and remembered fondly after his passing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is a young child who is loved by Bob Cratchit and is the focus of their affectionate dialogue."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tiny Tim is portrayed as a frail but loved child of Bob Cratchit who participates enthusiastically in the family's Christmas celebration despite his health condition."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DECEASED MAN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
