    <node id="&quot;BOB CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk mentioned in passing."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk who celebrates Christmas Eve enthusiastically despite his lowly position."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk who earns fifteen 'bob' a week and has a four-roomed house with his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, described as being in a dismal little cell beyond his master's counting-house. His fire is very small due to Scrooge's control over the coal-box."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's employee whom he treats kindly after his transformation, sending him a large turkey for Christmas dinner."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's underpaid clerk who is described as cold but warmer than Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a kind-hearted individual who is patient and mild, shown through his interactions with Tiny Tim."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is depicted as a kind and caring father who is concerned about his family's well-being."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is described as a kind-hearted man who works for Ebenezer Scrooge, struggling with his low pay but maintaining a positive attitude."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is mentioned as Scrooge's clerk, whom Scrooge wishes to speak to."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is mentioned as a character from Scrooge's past, with whom he shares a conversation while they walk together."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the clerk to Ebenezer Scrooge and a loving father to his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the father in the story, working at Scrooge's company and struggling financially but being kind and loving to his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the father of the Cratchit family, struggling financially but filled with love and compassion for his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit, Scrooge's underpaid and overworked employee who has a large family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit, the husband of Mrs. Cratchit, is shown to be a proud father who leads his family in celebrating Christmas with great care and enthusiasm."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob is Scrooge's underpaid employee who receives a salary raise from Scrooge after their interaction on Christmas morning."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7</data>
    </node>
