      <data key="d1">"Jacob Marley appears as a ghost to Ebenezer Scrooge on Christmas Eve, warning him about his future."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley appears as a ghost to Scrooge, emphasizing the importance of charity and kindness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner who appears as a ghost to warn him about the consequences of his greedy lifestyle."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is mentioned as the one who predicted Scrooge's encounter with the Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is mentioned in relation to his burial and the sexton's spade. He is presumably deceased and has some connection to Scrooge."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley is the deceased former business partner of Ebenezer Scrooge, appearing as a ghost to warn him about his future."&lt;SEP&gt;"Jacob Marley was Scrooge's partner in life, now appearing as a ghost to warn Scrooge."</data>
