    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S NEPHEW&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge's nephew is cheerful and merry, contrasting with his uncle's miserly attitude. He interacts directly with Scrooge in this scene."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's nephew is hosting a Christmas party with games, music, and good spirits. He plays blind man's-buff and Yes and No game."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's nephew is portrayed as jovial and generous, often laughing and encouraging others to do so. He has a positive relationship with his family but expresses mixed feelings towards Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CORNHILL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cornhill is a street where Bob Cratchit goes down a slide to celebrate Christmas Eve."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MERRY CHRISTMAS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Merry Christmas is a celebration observed by many, but Scrooge finds no joy in it initially."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCHOOLMASTER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The schoolmaster is portrayed as stern and ferocious, creating a dreadful state of mind in Master Scrooge."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE SPIRIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Spirit is a benevolent figure who guides Scrooge through his past experiences, aiming to evoke change in him."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit is a supernatural entity that guides Scrooge through various scenes from the past, present, and future."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Spirit is depicted as a joyous entity that brings happiness and brightness wherever it goes during Christmas Eve."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE GHOST OF CHRISTMAS PRESENT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of Christmas Present appears as a manifestation in Scrooge's room, offering guidance and teaching him lessons."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present appears to Scrooge and influences his emotions through music and memories."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present shows Scrooge scenes from the past, present, and future to teach him about life and charity."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Ghost of Christmas Present takes Scrooge on a journey to different locations, showing him various scenes of celebration and hardship."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE TABLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The table is where the mother lays her work and where the family gathers for their conversation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;JACOB MARLEY'S GHOST&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Jacob Marley's Ghost is a spectral apparition that visits Scrooge to warn him about his future fate if he doesn't change his ways."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OLD JOE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Old Joe is a scavenger who appraises items brought by others, showing lack of remorse for their actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Old Joe is involved in sorting through items taken from the deceased man's belongings."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WEALTH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wealth is mentioned as an idol that has displaced the Fairy, which Scrooge seems to regret."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE'S NIECE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scrooge's niece is participating in the games at the Christmas party. She is skilled at How, When, and Where game and loves her love to admiration with all the letters of the alphabet."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's niece is pretty and expressive, often reacting indignantly or with humor to her uncle's behavior. She shares a close bond with her sisters and has a strong opinion about Scrooge's character."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAROLINE CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Caroline Cratchit shows relief at the news of her husband's creditor being dead, but feels guilty afterwards."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCHOOL&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The school mentioned is not quite deserted and has a solitary child left behind during Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;BELLE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Belle is Scrooge's fiancée who leaves him because of his growing meanness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Belle is Scrooge's former fiancée, now married with a child. She is described as graceful and full of promise."&lt;SEP&gt;"Belle is an old sweetheart of Scrooge's who ended their relationship due to his obsession with money and business."&lt;SEP&gt;"Belle is mentioned as someone who once loved Scrooge but left him due to his changed nature and greed."&lt;SEP&gt;"Isabella, Scrooge's former fiancée who broke off their engagement due to his obsession with money."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;UNCLE SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Initially described as an animal and later revealed to be Fred's uncle, Scrooge. He is the focus of the guessing game and later becomes the subject of a toast."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE HOB&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The hob is where Mrs. Cratchit keeps Bob's tea ready for him."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE THREE SPIRITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Three Spirits are supernatural beings who visit Scrooge on consecutive nights, each revealing different aspects of his past, present, and future."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCAVENGING&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Scavenging refers to the practice of searching for and collecting items from the dead, portrayed here as morally questionable."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HOLLY, MISTLETOE, RED BERRIES, IVY, TURKEYS, GEESE, GAME, POULTRY, BRAWN, MEAT, PIGS, SAUSAGES, OYSTERS, PIES, PUDDINGS, FRUIT, PUNCH&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"These items represent the typical foods and decorations associated with Christmas."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TOPPER&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Topper is a member of Scrooge's nephew's family who participates in blind man's-buff game. He pretends to be blind but knows where the plump sister is."&lt;SEP&gt;"Topper is introduced as Scrooge's nephew's friend, with an apparent interest in one of Scrooge's nieces. He joins in the laughter and merriment but does not express any significant opinions or actions."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE DEBT COLLECTORS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
