      <data key="d1">"The Ghost appears in Scrooge's room on Christmas Eve, serving as a catalyst for Scrooge's transformation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WANT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"CATEGORY"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Want is depicted as a girl clinging to the Spirit, appealing for assistance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Want is described as a girl who clings to the Spirit, representing the suffering caused by poverty and desperation."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GHOST OF CHRISTMAS YET TO COME&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come shows Scrooge a grim vision of the future if he continues on his current path."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;THE OFFICE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The location where Scrooge works and interacts with Bob Cratchit."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;TWO YOUNG CRATCHITS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON (PLURAL)"</data>
      <data key="d1">"The two young Cratchits are portrayed as lively and imaginative children who worry about the safety of the Christmas pudding."&lt;SEP&gt;"The two young Cratchits are siblings who kiss little Bob and share in his happiness."</data>
