    <node id="&quot;MARLEY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Jacob Marley, Scrooge's former business partner, whose ghost visits Scrooge to warn him about his future."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is Scrooge's former business partner, who has died but continues to be referenced in relation to their shared past."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is described as Scrooge's deceased business partner, appearing as a ghost seven years after his death."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley was Scrooge's deceased partner, whose face appears on the door knocker, indicating a past connection and possible supernatural presence."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley was Scrooge's partner who died seven years ago on this night."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">Ebenezer Scrooge, the protagonist of this story, is initially portrayed as a miserly and inhospitable businessman. He interacts with the ghost of Jacob Marley, his former partner, who warns him about his greedy ways. Scrooge is known for refusing to contribute to charitable causes at Christmas, including those related to the poor. He prefers his own company and dislikes the holiday season, finding it melancholy.

However, after being visited by three ghosts on Christmas Eve—Marley's Ghost, the Ghost of Christmas Past, Present, and Yet to Come—Scrooge undergoes a profound transformation. These encounters cause him fear, reflection, astonishment, and eventually, regret for his past actions.

During his visits with the spirits, Scrooge revisits key moments from his life, including his time working under his former boss Fezziwig, who was generous and kind-hearted. He also sees the impacts of his miserly ways on others, particularly his long-suffering employee Bob Cratchit and his family.

Initially out of his wits while reliving his past, Scrooge becomes animated in defense of Fezziwig's generosity. After witnessing his own future grave and being shown visions of Ignorance and Want, he experiences remorse and decides to change his ways.

On Christmas Day, Scrooge walks through his rooms, ensuring all is right before locking himself in for the night. Surprised by Marley's ghost appearing before him, Scrooge eventually accepts the lessons from the spirits. He becomes thoroughly good-natured, enjoying the company of his family during their Christmas celebration.

Scrooge's transformation is marked by his newfound kindness and generosity towards others, particularly Cratchit and his family. He makes amends for his past actions, proving that even the most miserly among us can change for the better.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19fcf3bed0b4df750efc07831690f550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683</data>
