      <data key="d4">"Scrooge is haunted by Marley's ghost after his death, leading him to reflect on his own life and actions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge sees Marley's face on the door knocker, suggesting a connection between them and possibly Scrooge's guilt or remorse."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge sees the ghost of his deceased business partner, Marley, which frightens him."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge was Marley's sole executor and administrator after his death, indicating their close business relationship during life."</data>
